            subtree.update_rectangles(sub_rect)
            x += subtree_width
    else:
        for i, subtree in enumerate(self._subtrees):
            subtree_height = int(subtree.data_size / total_size * height)
            if i == len(self._subtrees) - 1:
                subtree_height = y + height - subtree.rect[1]
            sub_rect = (x, y, width, subtree_height)
            subtree.update_rectangles(sub_rect)
            y += subtree_height
```
This implementation follows the treemap algorithm as described in the prompt. It divides the area into vertical or horizontal rectangles depending on the width and height of the input rectangle. The function is called recursively for each subtree.

